social_posts.post_text:
#FitBy50 Update - I am not just focused on my physical health, but also spiritual and mental health. Reading The Bible and journaling has been an essential component of my morning routine. This Sunday at Journey Church I shared about the 5 things as I read the Bible/Journal: Discern, Learn, Practice, Reflect and Celebrate. 

What’s your favorite way to read the Bible and journal? I’d love to hear your thoughts in the comments below👇

Congratulations to the newly married Mr & Mrs Lentz! We can't wait to watch God unfold His story in and through your lives and marriage! It was such an honor to officiate your wedding. Jennifer and I love you guys!

For we are his workmanship, created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand, that we should walk in them.” — Ephesians 2:10

Who is grateful that they have been created by God for good works? If you’re thankful that Jesus saved us, share this with someone and drop an “AMEN” in the comments! 🙌
Stay tuned ⏳
I love our dream team and the entire Journey Family! Can’t imagine spending Sunday mornings any other way.

Bring everything to God, and say, “God it’s yours. I’m open handed.”

What a message Pastor Jim brought this weekend! If you missed it, you can watch “Aware of God’s Presence: Prayer” now on Youtube.
Happy birthday to the love of my life! We celebrate you and the gift of God that you are to so many.
I love getting to lead Staff Meeting alongside my better half 🫶🏼
Today I trained harder than ever…untill tomorrow! #fitby50
Cheering on my friend Andrew Berry and our hometown Browns this afternoon! 🟫🟧
Pastor Jennifer and I loved visiting with all of our Journey Kids at Open Door School for Pastor Appreciation.

Today, @joelwilkess we celebrate not only your incredible journey but also the remarkable man of God you have become and continue to grow into. 🙏🙌 Your family stands by your side, cheering you on with unwavering support as you uncover the incredible plan that God has in store for your life. 💕
Keep learning, growing, and spreading love, son! 🌟🎁🎈 #HappyBirthday #BlessingsOnBlessings #ProudParents #hustleGRITstayHUMBLE
It was an honor getting to preach alongside my youngest son! Incredibly proud of you and the message you brought this weekend at @journeypeople.
We are ONE DAY away from Code Red! What are you praying and hoping will come out of tomorrow night? Drop your prayer request in the comments below so that our team can pray alongside you! 👏🏽
We are only one day away from our Thursday Night Service! Invite your friends and family and join us tomorrow night at 7PM at the Avon Campus for our “Sunday on a Thursday” experience! 👏

Hey parents & students! Tickets to THE WKND Youth Retreat are FREE until midnight! You will not want to miss out on THE WKND happening this Friday & Saturday at our Avon Campus, so make sure you visit Journey.church/events to register for free 🚨

“We must learn to display grace instead of being driven by performance. Let’s slow down and sit at the feet of Jesus regularly.”

Thank you Pastor Jim for bringing a timely message as we kick off our Legacy Series. Drop in the comments what you took away from today’s message!
It’s important to sow the right things. Our job as pastors and church leaders is to plant and water the right things as we follow the leading of the Holy Spirit.
Discipline equals freedom! Down 24 pounds feeling great! #fitby50 #9months2go

We are honored to participate in the “NFL My Cause My Cleats” initiative during the New England Patriots' game this afternoon. Thank you Coach Joe Kim for wearing these shoes and for supporting the Joshua Tree Behavioral Health Center! 

The shoes will be auctioned following the game to support Joshua Tree in its mission to help each person take their next step toward wholeness and freedom from mental health and substance abuse challenges. For more information on the Joshua Tree Behavioral Health Center, please visit Joshuatreehealth.com

Our heart is to bring hope to our local communities! We operate our local outreach initiatives through the Hope Exchange and Joshua Tree Behavioral Health Center.

This Sunday’s Legacy Offering will go towards expanding the staff and reach of Joshua Tree and towards Hope Exchange initiatives.
Frustrated that you can’t make habits stick? You don’t have to wait for January 1st to work on yourself! Here are some tips that you can implement starting right NOW.

LEGACY SUNDAY IS TOMORROW! 

I can’t wait to gather as a church as we take a huge leap forward in accelerating the vision! Our annual Legacy Offering equips us to step into the God-sized opportunities that lie ahead of us in 2024.

Who is grateful today that Jesus found you and makes you whole? 🙌

If you missed out on church this weekend, you can watch “The Blessing of Generosity” now on YouTube!
Thank you to our incredible Dream Team who brought hope to our communities this morning! We delivered 7,000 toys to 1,700 families around the Greater Cleveland area. Give Hope, Get Hope!
Thank you Journey Church for bringing hope to families who wouldn’t normally have Christmas. We were able to deliver 7,000 toys to 1,700 families around Greater Cleveland today! 🎁🧸
Thankful for Ramon helping me look good before the holidays! If you’re in the Cleveland area and need a great barber, make sure you hit him up. @tol_barbershop

CHRISTMAS PRAYER DECLARATION 👏🎄 While Christmas is often filled with joy and celebration, it can also be a difficult time for a lot of us. The holidays can bring anxiety around finances, loneliness, grief, and difficult family dynamics. If that’s you, I want you to pray this prayer with me and SHARE it with 3 friends. It may just be the encouragement they need!  #pray #prayer #jesus #christmas

“For God did not send his Son into the world to condemn the world, but to save the world through Him.” - John 3:17

Merry Christmas, Journey! 🎄 We love you and are praying over you during this holiday season 🤍

“Peace isn’t found in the absence of problems. It’s found in the presence of God.” 🙌🔥

If you missed this weekend’s message, you can catch “You Can Find Peace in 2024” now on YouTube! Click the link in our bio 🔗

This Christmas at Journey will be one I never forget. On behalf of Pastor Jennifer and I, thank you to every single member of our Dream Team and Journey Staff who made this Christmas memorable! Countless individuals encountered the peace and joy throughout the weekend that can only be found through Jesus!

As we gear up for year-end giving, let’s rejoice in some Kingdom Wins from 2023:

- 447 lives saved
- Distributed 700 turkeys and 24,000 lbs of food during our Thanksgiving Outreach
- Delivered 7,000 toys to families in our Christmas outreach
- Launched the Joshua Tree Behavior Health Center
- Sponsored 50 students for youth camp

Remember, all year-end gifts must be submitted by this Sunday, December 31st, at 11:59 pm. Visit the LINK in our bio to contribute. Your prayers, service, and generosity are deeply appreciated!

We are going to CRUSH IT in 2024! This upcoming year, I am putting a strong focus on my health; my mental, physical, spiritual, and relational health. Drop in the comments what you are prioritizing in 2024 and let's make it happen!
We are thanking God for everything He did through our church in 2023! We are also celebrating in advance for everything He is going to do in this new year. The best is yet to come! 🙌

As we enter in this new year, we can’t help but thank God for everything He did in 2023 through our church. We are praying that 2024 is full of breakthrough, provision, growth, encounters with God, and life giving moments!

Journey Church! The start of our 21 Days of Prayer & Fasting is right around the corner ✨

To get you ready, here’s your guide to fasting. Join us for our 21 DAYS OF PRAYER & FASTING starting next Wednesday, January 10th! 

Visit the link in our bio to subscribe to our daily devotionals and content for the 21 days 🔗

#21DaysofPrayer #21DoPF

Looking to be equipped for everything God has for you in 2024? 🙏 

Join us for #21DaysofPrayer and Fasting as we draw near to God. 

Click the link in our bio for resources on prayer and fasting and to subscribe to our daily devotionals 🔗

There are some miracles that will only happen because you move! ✨

“When she heard about Jesus, she came up behind him in the crowd and touched his cloak, because she thought, “if I just touch his clothes, I will be healed.” — Mark 5:27-28

The wait is finally over! We are so excited to kick off our 21 Days of Prayer & Fasting! Today’s prayer topic is Surrender 🙏

Surrender signifies giving up control and trusting God completely. Choosing to follow Him involves yielding control, exemplified in Jesus’ bold prayer in Matthew 6:10 for God’s kingdom and will on earth.

If you haven’t subscribed to our 21 Days of Prayer & Fasting, make sure you click the link in our bio or visit Journey.church/21days so you don’t miss out on our morning devotionals and additional resources 🔗 #21daysofprayer #pray #prayer

Code Red - Night One … “You are who God says you are!” @jimwilkes … #2024 is about to be 🔥 

@journeypeople

Miracles occur when we are desperate for a move of God in our lives! Code Red kicked off this week with a powerful night of worship, where we witnessed God’s power through prayer and miracles ✨ We’ll see you next Wednesday for our next Code Red at the Avon Campus!

Today’s prayer topic is Family & Relationships 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦

Hey parents, have you ever asked yourself the question, “how can I pray for my child or children?” Since today’s prayer topic is Family & Relationships, we wanted to provide some tips on how to pray for your kids. To access today’s full devotional, visit Journey.church/21days

Someone once asked me, “what would you tell the 20 year old version of yourself?” While I’m sure I’d spend hours with him sharing everything I’ve learned throughout my life, here are some of the essentials.

“So Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego came out of the fire…they saw that the fire had not harmed their bodies, nor was a hair of their heads singed…”

Sometimes the safest place to be is in the fire 🔥 What an impactful word from Pastor Jim last week at Code Red. But GUESS WHAT? We are only 24 hours away from Code Red tomorrow night at the Avon Campus! 🚨
Yesterday marked an emotional timestamp for our family… I am now 6 years CANCER FREE!!! God is good. God is faithful. Thank you Lord 🙏🏼
